## Priority: token efficiency over speed

When exploring code or narrowing behavior, optimize for **fewer tokens in the
conversation**, not for the fastest-looking answer. Prefer targeted retrieval,
smaller payloads, and one clear pass over the relevant path instead of wide reads
or repeated full-file dumps.

**Use jCodemunch MCP** for discovery and navigation (for example `plan_turn`,
`search_symbols`, `get_file_outline`, `get_symbol_source`, `find_references`,
`search_text`). Follow `.cursor/rules/jcodemunch.mdc` for the full workflow,
including when `Read` is required before edits.

The same priority for humans and copy-paste into global Cursor rules lives in
`USER_RULES.md` under **PRIORITY: TOKEN EFFICIENCY OVER SPEED**. If anything
conflicts, this file plus `jcodemunch.mdc` govern agent behavior; keep
`USER_RULES.md` aligned when workflow changes.

Treat whole-file reads and broad text scans as **last resort** when jCodemunch
cannot answer the question.
